      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">EM vs EN: Typographic Siblings</h2>
      <p>Both EM and EN are valid Scrabble words from the world of typography. Here's how they compare:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">EM — 4 points</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">E=1, M=3. Width of letter M. Used in em-dash (—) and em-space. The stronger play at double EN's score.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">EN — 2 points</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">E=1, N=1. Width of letter N (half an em). Used in en-dash (–). Scores half of EM but still valid.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

